                            <comment id="13788632" author="sushanth" created="Mon, 7 Oct 2013 22:00:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching patch to make SBAP mimic the old HdfsAuthorizationProvider for user-level  authorization&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13788677" author="sushanth" created="Mon, 7 Oct 2013 23:04:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Available workaround : If the problem is observed in hcat commandline, then instead of running hcat -e &apos;show databases;&apos;, run hive -e &apos;show databases;&apos;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If using webhcat in secure mode, then there&apos;s no way to get around it using hcat, then in that case, the suggested workaround would be to disable client-side authorization or SBAP on client-side to get around this problem. Metastore-side authorization can still be used.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13791983" author="sushanth" created="Thu, 10 Oct 2013 21:06:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Verifiable by setting hive.security.authorization.manager to SBAP and turning client-side auth on before running hcat -e &quot;show databases;&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13792006" author="sushanth" created="Thu, 10 Oct 2013 21:32:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also, note that this is currently tested by e2e tests REST_DDL_DB_4 in hcatalog/src/test/e2e/templeton/tests/ddl.conf when SBAP is used.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
